Djokovic Beats Federer 6-3, 6-3 for Third Consecutive Dubai Tennis Title

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-02-26T19:41:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-26/djokovic-beats-federer-6-3-6-3-for-third-consecutive-dubai-tennis-title.html
Novak Djokovic defeated  Roger
Federer  6-3, 6-3 to win the Dubai Championships for the third
consecutive year.  It’s the second title of the season for the Djokovic,
ranked third by the ATP Tour, and 20th of his career. It’s also
the 23-year-old Serb’s second straight victory over No. 2
Federer, after beating the Swiss en route to capturing the
Australian Open title last month.  Djokvic joins Federer as the only players to win three
consecutive titles in Dubai.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  